column5: Going to give it a shot once or twice this week, looks like we will be breaking ice!  I hate winter  !
Now we are definitely heading down Wednesday and again on Sat.  I really hope they are biting half as much as they were this past Sat.

We decided to head to Quinte today instead of Sunday due to the forcast weather and boy are we ever glad we did.  Picked up Eric at 5am headed to Terrys' and then met Sheldon at 6am and headed to the bay.  Once again we had the privilage to join Sheldon for the day in his boat due to clients cancelling, they really should have gone out!  Hit the water around 8:30am and quickly got set up with an eight rod spread!  Man this is really an advantage.  Anyway to make a long story short we had our best day on Quinte so far.  We went 16 for 19, and all quality fish.  So here is a bunch of fish porn, hope you enjoy, what a fun day and  we also had 3 double headers.                                               Cant wait till the next outing,  Once again thank you very much Sheldon for giving us the privilage of joining you for the day, it was a blast and it was nice to see you relaxed and having fun and actually gedtting to catch fish!
WOW,  More than impressed.  Good people with a knowledge of the area!  Congrats!
nicely done fellas...put on a show out there   Hawk
Very impressive indeed. All quality fish and lots of them. Congrats to you...you worked at it, you deserve the success. Thank you for posting.
Looks like a helluva day out there!!! Congrats!  I hope our G2G boys did well too!

Nice day you guys had out there Don...the fish were on, the winds were low, the temps were in the double digits.....what more could ya ask for  NIce pics...  Billy Bones and I are headin' down to Quinte this Wednesday...sure hope they stay hungry
WOW!!! That is one CRAZY day!!!!! Congrats on an amazing day out there...some real nice eyes in those pics!
Oustanding Badge and Co.!!  :clapping:
EPIC!
Wow. That's a day you guys won't forget anytime soon. Congrats..
WOW!!!  Now that is a good day of eye fishin.  Congrats on all the big fish
Great report and awesome pics  Don  Congratulations to all of you  Thanks for sharing Leechman
you know that sound a ruler makes when you hang it off the end of the desk and flick it!
serious numbers man !!....It's funny how being soaking wet and freezing cold has no effect when your hitting fish one after another !!!

We heard alot of chatter over the radio and guys were getting fish.  Where we were we counted 25 boats around us.  Fishindevil and the guys he was with pulled up close to us just as we hit our 3rd double header!  Hope everyone did well.  Man the rain was a bit of a pain again but to tell you the truth I like fishing out there when the winds are not high and its cloudy rainy and at least somewhat mild.    At least yesterday!
Congrads guys you all did good!
nicely done, I am what they call MEGA JEALOUS
Hey Don great report nice fish we saw you guys out there.  Don't worry I will have a report with fishes this evening GCD.  MTP
Nice going.  Thanks for the report.
Nice fish!

Awesome fishing don !!!!...and yes you are right it was the best fishing yet,hey you can see dans lund in the background with myself & brian besides you guys,some very big walleyes this weekend bud well done !!!...cheers
Yeah Shawn that was on of the double headers we go, just as you guys were pulling up.  I can only hope to have half as good a day on the next trip.

Was a great day out on the water, lots of chatter on the radio but it sounded like many where fishing 50 feet down. A majority of our big fish came high with reef runner 800s only 45 and 75 feet behind the boards.  -sheldon
Man o man some nice ones, WTG...
exactly!
